node.text:
what are your favourite ways to give someone a non body based compliment?
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it's my favourite way to compliment my friends and family! people are so much more than their body! 
compliments are free, from the heart and have the #PowerToTransform someone’s mood! I’m excited to partner with @Pantene on this campaign because I truly believe compliments have the power to transform someone’s day.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
compliments actually go a long way in CONNECTING ourselves to others. A @pantene study found that 77% of canadians have felt disconnected from their friends and family during this time and yet 79% of canadians found a compliment can go a LONG way to making them feel better.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
compliments that are genuine are never superficial and never get old. on top of that, we should be giving them to ourselves too! 
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
make someone's day a bit brighter! #PowerToTransform #partner #ad

node.text:
Have you ever been bullied or harassed online? #PlanCanadaPartner 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This #DayoftheGirl, I’m joining @PlanCanada to shine a light on the harassment and
abuse girls face on social media. Every day girls are physically threatened, racially abused, sexually harassed and body shamed.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Girls from across the world have written an open letter to Instagram, Facebook, TikTok and Twitter, calling on them to create stronger and more effective ways to report abuse and harassment. Sign their open letter now – link in my story – and show that thousands of people stand with girls #FreeToBeOnline online, they’ll be taken seriously #StoptheSetback

node.text: my general take on what’s happening as of now. of course i didn’t get to say everything that i wanted to say and didn’t say everything right. it is a WILD time that we are living in. be prepared to be uncomfortable. be grateful we all still have internet, running water and food. (some of us actually still don’t have those things) and most of all, be grateful we have each other. it sounds corny as hell, but you don’t have your food or toilet paper or internet or water without the help of another human. don’t buy 250 rolls of toilet paper, it’s not the diarrhea boogeyman coming for you. also, what happens after this? do we go back to normal life? will there be a normal life? do you even WANT your normal life back? this is going to be a huge shift for many of us. your emotional shit is going to come up because we don’t have the same comforts as before. be kind and stay vigilant and stay aware! ✌️💕

It’s going to be summer in a few months! (we need some sunshine, don’t we?!) ☀️💫 #ad
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This is your annual reminder that you may see all different types of bodies rocking swimsuits.
Hairy bodies.
Big/fat bodies.
Scarred bodies.
Disabled bodies.
Etc.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
The universe didn’t slave away for 13.8 billion years just so we could place a restrictions on what looks good vs what doesn’t. You are a really awesome cosmic creature and you deserve to enjoy this season as much as anyone else.
Wear the bikini.
Go to the beach.
Eat the food.
Live that life without hiding.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
You really really deserve it and remind those around you that they deserve it too! 👙🌸
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Wearing all the amazing @torrid #torrid
#bikinibody #summerbody #bodygoals #allbodiesaregoodbodies

node.text:
when i moved back in with my dad and step mom in april, i would often do this.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i felt like the car gave me some type of quietness that the inside of the house couldn’t. sometimes i would listen to my music fade off, other times i would scroll instagram and sometimes i would just put my head on the steering wheel.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i love the weird things we do to try and self soothe.

node.text:
i get this question a lot in private.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“how can i reveal myself more?
what if they don’t like what they see?
how did you do it?
i’ve never let anyone see me in the light.
i don’t think they will accept me.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
first things first, anyone who wants to be with you physically has LOOKED at you. like, really looked! and they obviously like what they see and nothing else about you will turn them off. and in the rare instance that it does, it’s their problem. not yours. forever not yours.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
communicating with partners about what makes us feel insecure is important. and also what makes us feel desired. if there are certain ways you want to be desired that you feel too insecure to initiate, take little steps and ask for your partners help.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
find out what makes you feel free and liberated. just because this is tender and difficult doesn’t mean that it’s impossible. it just means it might take a while.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
there’s also no rush whatsoever. honouring where you’re at while also wanting to be somewhere different is a whole thing ❤️🔥
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
you deserve to be seen and to be loved.

node.text:
which diet would you like me to be on so i can make you more comfortable with my body?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
what can i comply to so you will feel like i am a “good” person?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
would i make you more comfortable if i never ate bread? if i only started eating at 4PM?
if i juiced celery?
if i bought things that have no fat in them?
if i made sure i ate potatoes instead of pasta?
if i only ate certain types of greens?
if they were only grown in a certain place with no pesticides or herbicides?
if i never ate yogurt or tofu or had salad dressing or anything “processed”?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
would you be able to show me the diet that worked?
would you be able to show me the diet that healed the millions?
the diet that ended all strife we have with our bodies?
the diet that cured all ailments?
that has a 100% success rate?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
you can’t.
because it doesn’t exist.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

"You're so dramatic." "Quit being so sensitive." "Go ahead and throw yourself another pity party." "You're making a big deal out of nothing." Who is with me?'.

node.text:
did you hear any of these growing up?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the “quit being so sensitive” one ruined me. i was so sensitive and anxious growing up it was like i couldn’t turn off my alarms or my imagination. which are both some how connected. my sensitivity gave me access to creativity, empathy and depth of experience. i didn’t just like people i loved them. i didn’t just enjoy nature, i could feel it in every part of my body. there was never just one story in my head but thousands. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but the same was true for pain. it was never just “goodbye see you next week” it was “what if next week never comes?” “what if you didn’t show up like that one time?” if someone at school didn’t like me it was the end of my world. if it was pain on some part of my body, my whole being felt it instead. i couldn’t turn it off.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it’s only been in the last few years that’s i’ve learned that sensitivity isn’t a bad thing, especially once you are able to regulate and have a dialogue with it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but holy fuck. was it ever stigmatized with the whole “quit being so sensitive.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i also go the “you’re so dramatic” and “you make a big deal out of everything.”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
little by little, we undo what was said and done 🪡 🧵
via @sitwithwhit

node.text:
i used to be so *embarrassed* about my body.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
embarrassed like it did something wrong. there would be times i would even apologize for it, simply for existing.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“i’m sorry about my scars”
“i’m so sorry about my stretch marks”
“i’m sorry my breasts”
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
covering up and hiding felt so safe and so good. people would make fun of me for wearing sweaters in the summertime and partners would beg to see my body beyond the sheets and in the light, but i didn’t care. i would take any joke and i would lose any person if it meant that i could stay covered.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i would tell partners to leave if they didn’t like it. it would actually be better if they did, i work best on my own. hidden. alone. away.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but eventually there’s a little voice that just won’t shut up. it says stuff about love, about dreams, about the world and it begs you to explore. to be touched. to be adored. to be seen.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in small moments you shut it up or you quietly listen. and in the moments you quietly listen your shame, guilt and hatred begin to transform into curiosity, love and passion.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it’s okay if you’re not there yet either! it takes a thousand moments of listening to that small voice and choosing the unknown, over and over and over again ❤️
#selfgrowth #selflovejourney #youareloved
